additional_house_rules:
Please respect my neighbors by limiting noise during your stay. Please no music after 8pm. 

Please remove your shoes inside the apartment.

All children including infants are counted as guests and subject to the extra guest charge if the total number of occupants is greater than 4 people.

If you make a mess in the kitchen, please clean up after yourself. I also request all guests recycle (it's the law) and take out the trash if it's full. 

A few things I do not permit: no pets, no smoking, no guests that have not been approved by me, and no parties (any gathering of individuals not included in the reservation).

I am flexible with check in & check out times if I do not have guests before or after your reservation. If I do, then the standard check in time is 3pm and the check out time is 11am.

Reservations made using Instant Book may not start or end on major US Holidays including Thanksgiving Day, Christmas Eve, Christmas Day, New Years Eve, New Years Day. Your reservation will be cancelled if you attempt to make a reservation that violates this rule without first contacting me.

You are responsible for replacing any damaged or missing items during your stay including, but not limited to: sheets, towels, and glasses. I request anyone wearing makeup use the the makeup removal wash cloths to avoid staining the white towels. The complete inventory including replacement prices is included in the house manual binder in the apartment.
description:
Floor-to-ceiling windows provide breathtaking views of Midtown Manhattan from this designer 2-bedroom / 2-bath penthouse apartment. Experience true luxury throughout: granite countertops in kitchen and both bathrooms, hardwood floors, high-end modern furnishings, Kiehl's bath products, Nespresso machine, Riedel glasses, 5-star hotel quality linens, Casper mattresses, and more. Near all the major Midtown tourist destinations and convenient to most of Manhattan's best restaurants and nightlife.

Amenities:

I believe my guests deserve the best and don't skimp on anything. Just a few highlights: amazing high-tech mattress, Kiehl's bathroom products, well-equipped TV with Apple TV (100+ satellite channels, HBO Go, Netflix, Amazon Prime, and Hulu) and free Nespresso coffee/tea.

Bedroom 1: The most amazing mattress you've ever slept on! The Casper mattress conforms to you're body and accommodates every sleeping position, but you don't sink in so it's really easy to get up. It's super high-tech and designed by a company in NYC. The sheets and duvet cover are from Brooklinen. The TV has a Roku connected. Has an amazing view of the Empire State Building and other Midtown buildings.

Bedroom 2: The same queen Casper mattress and Brooklinen sheets as bedroom 1. Has an amazing view of the Hudson River.

Living Room: An LED Samsung TV and Apple TV with 100+ satellite channels, HBO Go, Netflix, Amazon Prime, and Hulu. I have lots of great books to read and NYC guidebooks to plan your daily activities. The mid-century modern sectional sofa comfortably sleeps 1 person. There is also a twin air mattress available if requested before your stay. The Saarinen tulip table seats 4 and there are 2 additional chairs in the bedrooms which can be used for additional seating.

Kitchen: It's fully equipped with nice appliances. Very large refrigerator by NYC standards. Built-in microwave and gas range. I have a Nespresso machine and tea for your use. There's also a toaster, pots & pans, ceramic knives, silverware, plates, bowls, water glasses, and Riedel wine & champagne glasses.

Bathrooms: You can pack light and leave your toiletries at home. The bathroom has luxury shampoo, conditioner, and body wash from Kiehl's. There's a huge medicine cabinet for storage in both bathrooms.

Other: Iron and ironing board, wood hangers, and air-conditioning.

Guests have access to all areas except one locked closet in the hallway. Each bedroom has a closet with hangers and available space for personal belongings/luggage.

Someone will be available 24/7 during your stay if you require assistance.

Hell's Kitchen is located in Midtown West. The neighborhood is known for it's restaurants and nightlife. It's also home to many Broadway theaters and adjacent to Times Square.

The nearest subway is the 50th Street C/E station, which is around a 10 minute walk. The station is 1 stop from 42nd St/Times Square where you can transfer to most other subway lines.
